# Spring Boot Patterns

> Project-specific patterns for the Todo backend.

## Entity (JPA)

```java
@Entity
@Table(name = "todos")
public class Todo {
    @Id
    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.IDENTITY)
    private Long id;
    private String title;
    private boolean completed;
    // getters, setters, constructors
}
```

## Repository

Use `JpaRepository` or `CrudRepository`:

```java
public interface TodoRepository extends JpaRepository<Todo, Long> {}
```

## REST Controller

- Use `@RestController` and `@RequestMapping("/api/todos")`
- Return `ResponseEntity` for proper status codes (201 Created, 204 No Content, 404 Not Found)
- Validate input at boundaries (e.g., `@Valid` with DTOs, or manual checks for empty title)

## Validation

- Reject empty or missing `title` on POST with `400 Bad Request`
- Return `404 Not Found` for PATCH/DELETE on non-existent id
- PATCH: accept partial payload; only update provided fields

## Response Codes

| Scenario | Status |
|----------|--------|
| GET list | 200 OK |
| POST create | 201 Created |
| PATCH update | 200 OK |
| PATCH/DELETE not found | 404 Not Found |
| DELETE success | 204 No Content |
| Invalid POST (empty title) | 400 Bad Request |
